          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ". The film is a beloved classic because it deftly intertwined screwball comedy and supernatural horror. But it also illustrated how the era’s conservative economic ideologies were often amplified by seemingly apolitical products like movies and TV shows — a development that still reverberates today.",
